  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Voulez Vous is a newly built five star hotel in <a data-udi="umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565" href="/{localLink:umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565}" title="Tignes">Tignes</a> le Lac. The hotel has a modern but traditional theme throughout with a mix of light and dark colours. The large windows give amazing clear views of the mountains. </p>
<h2>Great location </h2>
<p>The Voulez Vous is a 5* hotel located 50 meters away from the slopes, where you can pop your skis on and head down the short piste to the main lift station to make the most of the varied skiing in the <a data-udi="umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03}" title="Tignes-Val d’Isere Ski Area">Tignes-Val d'Isere Ski Area</a>.  The resort's bars, restaurants and shops are just a short walk away from the hotel, so you can pick up a souvenir or enjoy a drink or two at one of the bars.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>An amazing hotel wouldn't be finished without an amazing spa area. It includes a whirlpool, sauna and steam room, so you can give your achy ski legs a rest. There's also an infinity style swimming pool with uninterrupted views of the snowy mountain tops. For the fitness fanatics, there is also a fitness room onsite with a range of equipment available. </p>
<h2>Evening entertainment</h2>
<p>Food is a big part of any ski holiday and staying at the Voulez Vous is no different. Start your day at the extensive breakfast buffet which includes a variety of sweet and savoury options including mountain breads, regional cheeses and charcuterie, seasonal fruit, pastries and local delicacies. When it comes to dinner meals are taken in the Franco-Italian Il Savoia restaurant, which serves tasty dishes including fresh pasta, risottos and meats with ingredients sourced from local producers.  You also have the option to dine in a selection of other Etincelles restaurants in Tignes Le Lac - choose from Savoyard specialities at the historic Brasserie de L'Arbina or fresh seafood at Les Terrasses. </p>
<p>After your evening meal, unwind in the bar and lounge area with a drink or head to the karaoke room, and enjoy singing along to your favourite songs - can you remember the words?</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
